WEBVTT

00:04.221 --> 00:06.441
I think I'll get
another cup of tea.

00:09.792 --> 00:13.970
[ softly]
V-K-U-J-I-R.

00:14.057 --> 00:15.406
Jivku--

00:15.493 --> 00:17.626
a small, featherless bird
from southern Africa.

00:17.713 --> 00:19.149
Love you, son.

00:19.236 --> 00:21.499
Go ahead and blow off curfew
this weekend.

00:23.066 --> 00:26.983
Well, well, well, look
what we have here.

00:27.070 --> 00:28.854
I was just reading
about one of these...

00:28.941 --> 00:30.421
Jivku isn't a real word,

00:30.508 --> 00:32.293
but "Nazqweb" isn't
Viking toothpaste,

00:32.380 --> 00:34.512
and Mom got 162 points
for it.

00:38.864 --> 00:40.866
♪ Yes, no, maybe ♪

00:40.953 --> 00:44.218
♪ I don't know ♪

00:44.305 --> 00:47.569
♪ Can you repeat the question? ♪

00:47.656 --> 00:49.179
♪ You're not the boss
of me now ♪

00:49.266 --> 00:51.573
♪ You're not
the boss of me now ♪

00:51.660 --> 00:54.097
♪ You're not the boss
of me now ♪

00:54.184 --> 00:57.231
♪ And you're not so big ♪

00:57.318 --> 00:59.798
♪ You're not the boss
of me now ♪

00:59.885 --> 01:01.713
♪ You're not
the boss of me now ♪

01:01.800 --> 01:04.455
♪ You're not the boss
of me now ♪

01:04.542 --> 01:06.588
♪ And you're not so big ♪

01:06.675 --> 01:11.158
♪ Life is unfair. ♪

01:12.463 --> 01:13.856
I got to get to work.

01:13.943 --> 01:15.858
You make sure
your father gets out of bed.

01:15.945 --> 01:17.294
I don't why,

01:17.381 --> 01:18.643
but he hasn't slept
for the last four nights.

01:18.730 --> 01:20.036
So if you have to,
yell "fire."

01:20.123 --> 01:22.691
If that doesn't work, set one.

01:27.652 --> 01:30.133
Why would your mother buy me
pants without a zipper?

01:30.220 --> 01:31.743
Dad, you have
them on backwards.

01:31.830 --> 01:33.049
Oh.

01:33.136 --> 01:34.311
Malcolm, I need your help.

01:34.398 --> 01:35.921
Our 20th anniversary
is coming up

01:36.008 --> 01:37.880
and I've been going crazy
trying to think

01:37.967 --> 01:39.621
of the perfect gift
for your mother.

01:39.708 --> 01:42.406
It has gotta be something
really fantastic.

01:42.493 --> 01:43.451
And I've got nothing.

01:43.538 --> 01:45.017
Maybe you're trying too hard.

01:45.105 --> 01:46.671
Why don't you just do something
simple?

01:46.758 --> 01:49.935
You know, get a bottle
of champagne, watch a sunset,

01:50.022 --> 01:51.546
recite a poem to her.

01:51.633 --> 01:53.548
So you just use
the genius thing on yourself,

01:53.635 --> 01:54.462
is that it, son?

01:54.549 --> 01:55.680
Come on!

01:55.767 --> 01:57.508
This anniversary has got
to make up

01:57.595 --> 01:59.249
for 19 crappy celebrations.

01:59.336 --> 02:02.557
You have no idea the hell
I've put that woman through.

02:02.644 --> 02:06.126
[ playing martial music]

02:23.752 --> 02:27.147
I wish I could say that was
the low point of the day.

02:40.812 --> 02:42.727
Chad?

02:42.814 --> 02:44.816
Are you trying to make
Coach Cleary

02:44.903 --> 02:46.470
burst into flames again?

02:46.557 --> 02:47.863
[ kid makes revving sound]

02:47.950 --> 02:49.647
Dewey, Dewey, you
won't believe it!

02:49.734 --> 02:51.562
It's the most
amazing thing ever!

02:51.649 --> 02:53.303
We made friends
with a normal kid!

02:53.390 --> 02:55.087
He spoke to us
and everything!

02:55.175 --> 02:57.829
It was he-heep!
Hee-ca-ca--

02:57.916 --> 02:59.657
Calm down.

02:59.744 --> 03:01.659
Just breathe, okay?

03:01.746 --> 03:03.922
All this time
we thought he hated us!

03:04.009 --> 03:06.708
-Who is it?
-Kyle Rogers!

03:06.795 --> 03:09.711
He likes us so much
that he put both our names in

03:09.798 --> 03:11.365
to run for Student
Body President!

03:12.279 --> 03:13.410
He said he can't wait

03:13.497 --> 03:15.325
to hear our campaign speeches.

03:15.412 --> 03:16.674
-Really?
-ZOE: Yes!

03:16.761 --> 03:18.372
I feel like I'm in a dream,

03:18.459 --> 03:20.809
except there isn't
an armless scarecrow

03:20.896 --> 03:23.246
who can't stop crying.
This is so great!

03:23.333 --> 03:25.901
But we'll have to promise
that we'll both stay friends
no matter what happens.

03:25.988 --> 03:27.337
Don't worry, Zoe.

03:27.424 --> 03:29.600
We won't let anything
come between us,

03:29.687 --> 03:33.213
even though we're both competing
for this great honor.

03:37.173 --> 03:39.175
[ bell rings]

03:41.960 --> 03:46.443
Hey, Dewey, what'd you do,
rat me out to Mr. Myers?

03:46.530 --> 03:47.879
Of course not.

03:47.966 --> 03:49.577
I just figured
since you're so interested

03:49.664 --> 03:51.231
in the democratic process,

03:51.318 --> 03:52.971
I'd nominate you to run
for School President, too.

03:53.058 --> 03:55.017
-What?
-I gotta admit, it's clever

03:55.104 --> 03:57.585
making Hanson and Zoe run
for office.

03:57.672 --> 03:59.239
They're gonna be humiliated.

03:59.326 --> 04:01.023
The only thing
more humiliating

04:01.110 --> 04:02.590
would be losing to 'em.

04:04.679 --> 04:06.550
Ow! Leave it alone!

04:06.637 --> 04:09.205
Nobody one can even see
a zit back there.

04:09.292 --> 04:10.772
Stop squirming
so I can clean it.

04:10.859 --> 04:12.121
You know,
a little more effort

04:12.208 --> 04:14.036
on your personal grooming
wouldn't kill you.

04:14.123 --> 04:16.168
Sunday nights before bed
your father goes over

04:16.255 --> 04:18.257
every square inch of his body
with a hand mirror.

04:18.345 --> 04:19.998
Oh, my God.

04:20.084 --> 04:21.826
Do you remember
that summer seminar in Arizona

04:21.913 --> 04:23.306
I applied to last year?

04:23.393 --> 04:24.829
-Yeah, you didn't get it.
-I know, but somehow...

04:24.916 --> 04:26.701
my name was entered
as an alternate

04:26.788 --> 04:28.616
for a study-in-Europe program.

04:28.703 --> 04:31.575
The guy who was supposed to go
was bitten by a tick

04:31.662 --> 04:33.316
and now basically lives
in a hyperbaric chamber.

04:33.403 --> 04:34.491
So I get to go
in his place!

04:34.578 --> 04:35.884
Slow down, Malcolm.

04:35.971 --> 04:37.451
We can't afford
to help you with that.

04:37.538 --> 04:38.930
That's just it.
It's all paid for!

04:39.017 --> 04:41.498
I'm going to Paris,
Prague, Munich, Vienna.

04:41.585 --> 04:44.153
I'm gonna be staying
in castles!

04:44.240 --> 04:45.894
This is an incredible
opportunity.

04:45.981 --> 04:49.071
This is the luckiest thing
that's ever happened to me.

04:49.158 --> 04:51.813
I have to do something
to protect it.

04:51.900 --> 04:53.293
What?

04:53.380 --> 04:55.382
It's like I feel
I should balance it out somehow.

04:55.469 --> 04:57.209
You know, give something back
so I don't lose it.

04:57.297 --> 04:59.342
Listen to you.
Something wonderful happens

04:59.429 --> 05:00.909
and all you can think about

05:00.996 --> 05:03.172
is how the world's going
to take it away.

05:03.259 --> 05:05.957
You're growing up.

05:07.219 --> 05:09.309
[ mumbling]

05:13.574 --> 05:16.185
You, come with me.

05:16.272 --> 05:17.360
What are you doing?

05:17.447 --> 05:19.319
Dad, you have to understand.

05:19.406 --> 05:21.233
The reason I missed
so many days of school

05:21.321 --> 05:23.323
is that the calendar
on my watch stopped.

05:23.410 --> 05:24.802
I thought it was Saturday
all week!

05:24.889 --> 05:25.890
Put it on the shelf.

05:25.977 --> 05:27.675
The watch?
You want me...

05:27.762 --> 05:32.027
What am I going to do?
Your mother... it's horrible.

05:32.114 --> 05:34.246
Well, I don't know.
You married her.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.510
What about our anniversary?

05:36.597 --> 05:38.294
It won't fit!

05:38.381 --> 05:39.861
What about the anniversary?
What are you talking about?

05:39.948 --> 05:43.081
It's got to be... the best!

05:43.168 --> 05:44.561
Where is it?

05:44.648 --> 05:46.781
Are you still asleep?

05:46.868 --> 05:47.956
The dogs are right.

05:48.043 --> 05:50.132
I got to get her
a great present.

05:51.176 --> 05:53.918
Dad, your shoe's untied.

05:54.005 --> 05:55.224
Of course!

05:58.358 --> 05:59.576
Thank you.

06:00.969 --> 06:03.885
Yeah, you aregoing to have
to get her a good present.

06:03.972 --> 06:06.148
She's a great lady.

06:06.235 --> 06:08.019
In fact, I don't
know why,

06:08.106 --> 06:10.500
but she wants you
to give me $20.

06:13.242 --> 06:14.765
That's good.

06:16.332 --> 06:19.248
That's good. That's good.
She'll know what to do.

06:19.335 --> 06:21.163
-Thanks.
-I don't know the answer.

06:21.250 --> 06:22.991
Tell me. Tell me now!

06:23.078 --> 06:24.862
Okay, calm down.

06:24.949 --> 06:27.430
I think you're going to have
more success if you can relax,

06:27.517 --> 06:29.258
make me a BLT
with avocado,

06:29.345 --> 06:31.173
and open up a bag
of chips.

06:31.260 --> 06:33.436
Then you can sit at my feet
and purr while I eat.

06:33.523 --> 06:34.394
That's it!

06:36.657 --> 06:37.875
What are you
talking about?

06:37.962 --> 06:39.311
You've gotta vote for me!

06:39.399 --> 06:40.878
All those rumors you've heard
are lies!

06:40.965 --> 06:43.054
I don't want to have school
on Saturdays.

06:43.141 --> 06:45.100
And I don't wear pull-ups!

06:46.144 --> 06:47.407
I'm glad to see

06:47.494 --> 06:49.147
you're so pumped
about the election, Kyle.

06:49.234 --> 06:50.627
A lot of kids think

06:50.714 --> 06:52.281
they're too hip
for student government,

06:52.368 --> 06:54.544
but I think you'll find out
how exciting it can be

06:54.631 --> 06:57.286
once you organize
your first recycling drive.

07:00.289 --> 07:01.508
You know what, Zoe?

07:01.595 --> 07:03.423
I actually hope you win.

07:03.510 --> 07:06.817
Thanks, Hanson.
And I hope you win.

07:06.904 --> 07:09.690
Of course,
I can't speak for bad Zoe.

07:09.777 --> 07:12.257
Okay, Chad, see those
kids over there?

07:12.344 --> 07:14.346
They're friends of Kyle's.

07:14.434 --> 07:16.827
On election day,
it'd probably be better
if they didn't vote.

07:16.914 --> 07:18.350
Okay.

07:20.135 --> 07:22.616
Why don't you go back inside?
You don't want to see this.

07:24.879 --> 07:27.185
Hey, Mom, you know
when I said I was going
to give something back?

07:27.272 --> 07:28.665
Well, I was thinking.

07:28.752 --> 07:30.406
Maybe I could work
at a homeless shelter,

07:30.493 --> 07:32.843
or teach some kids how to read,
but then it came to me.

07:32.930 --> 07:35.585
I bought a guitar.

07:35.672 --> 07:37.848
-What?
-It's perfect.

07:37.935 --> 07:39.502
I mean, Dewey has this
incredible musical talent.

07:39.589 --> 07:41.243
I must have it, too.
I just haven't tried it yet.

07:41.330 --> 07:43.027
How long do you have
to return it?

07:43.114 --> 07:45.029
15 days.
But I'm not going to return it.

07:45.116 --> 07:46.466
Well, that'll be long enough

07:46.553 --> 07:48.032
for you to figure out
you can't do this.

07:48.119 --> 07:50.992
What are you talking about?

07:51.079 --> 07:52.167
I can play music if I want to.

07:52.254 --> 07:54.256
I'm sorry, honey.
You can't.

07:54.343 --> 07:55.736
Your brain doesn't work
that way.

07:55.823 --> 07:58.216
You don't have
that kind of creative spark.

07:58.303 --> 07:59.304
What?

07:59.391 --> 08:01.568
See, Dewey is a flier.

08:01.655 --> 08:02.699
He'll just drift and float
through life

08:02.786 --> 08:03.787
and things will turn out
for him.

08:03.874 --> 08:05.746
Now, you and I,
we're burrowers.

08:05.833 --> 08:07.748
We're at our best
when our heads are down,

08:07.835 --> 08:09.967
and we're grinding through
a mountain of drudgery.

08:10.054 --> 08:11.447
You don't know that.

08:11.534 --> 08:13.101
-Yes, I do.
-You actually think you know.

08:13.188 --> 08:14.798
what I'd be good at
before I even try it?

08:14.885 --> 08:15.930
That's right.

08:16.017 --> 08:17.671
Oh, really?
Then tell me,

08:17.758 --> 08:20.064
how would I be at scuba diving?
Or mountain climbing?

08:20.151 --> 08:21.631
Or flamenco dancing?

08:21.718 --> 08:23.720
Bad at scuba diving,
good at mountain climbing.

08:23.807 --> 08:25.374
Flamenco dancing?
A disaster.

08:25.461 --> 08:27.550
I'm not trying
to hurt your feelings.

08:27.637 --> 08:29.204
I'm just telling you
what I know.

08:29.291 --> 08:31.075
It's a good thing you weren't
John Lennon's mother.

08:31.162 --> 08:33.643
If I were John Lennon's mother,
he'd still be alive.

08:37.691 --> 08:39.736
-Hey, Reese.
-Hey, Dad.

08:39.823 --> 08:41.956
Oh, here.
I got you a new watch.

08:42.043 --> 08:44.698
-Thanks. What'd you do that for?
-I don't know.

08:44.785 --> 08:46.830
A thought just popped into
my head that you needed one.

08:46.917 --> 08:48.266
And you have no idea why?

08:48.353 --> 08:49.964
-Uh-uh.
-Wow.

08:50.051 --> 08:51.966
You gotta see this!
I finally found

08:52.053 --> 08:53.837
the perfect anniversary present
for your mom.

08:53.924 --> 08:57.232
She had this exact music box
when we were first married

08:57.319 --> 08:59.321
until your brother Francis
got a hold of it

08:59.408 --> 09:01.149
and smashed it
into a million pieces.

09:01.236 --> 09:03.412
Anyway, I'm walking through
this antique store

09:03.499 --> 09:05.327
in complete desperation,
and there it is:

09:05.414 --> 09:06.894
the same music box.

09:06.981 --> 09:08.722
Oh, what a relief.

09:08.809 --> 09:11.463
I am going to sleep
like a baby tonight.

09:15.729 --> 09:19.080
I have 15 days to learn how
to play this thing well enough

09:19.167 --> 09:21.169
to totally humiliate my mom.

09:21.256 --> 09:22.562
Seems doable.

09:28.655 --> 09:31.788
Doodly-doodly-doodly-doodly,
doo-doo-wah!

09:31.875 --> 09:33.616
[ imitates guitar riff]

09:33.703 --> 09:37.054
♪ Bo, bo-bo, bo-bo-bo-bo-bo ♪

09:37.141 --> 09:39.056
[ imitates guitar riff]

09:39.143 --> 09:41.406
♪ Bo! Bo-bo-bo-bo,
bo-bo-bo ♪

09:41.493 --> 09:43.452
♪ Doodly-doodly-doodly... ♪

09:43.539 --> 09:45.367
[ imitates guitar riff]

09:46.716 --> 09:48.892
I'm willing to forget
I ever saw this,

09:48.979 --> 09:51.242
if you tell me everything
you know about sleepwalking.

09:51.329 --> 09:54.115
Sleepwalking?

09:54.202 --> 09:55.812
Well, all I know is that
it's a dissociative state,

09:55.899 --> 09:57.684
-which basically...
-Just tell me what causes it.

09:57.771 --> 09:59.120
Well, there's a few things.

09:59.207 --> 10:01.383
It usually happens
when a person is under

10:01.470 --> 10:03.690
intense emotional
or psychological stress.

10:03.777 --> 10:06.170
So if a sleepwalker stays
stressed out,

10:06.257 --> 10:07.389
he'll continue sleepwalking?

10:07.476 --> 10:08.608
I don't know, probably.

10:08.695 --> 10:09.609
Beautiful.

10:18.487 --> 10:19.619
[ mimics guitar riff]

10:20.358 --> 10:21.838
[ loud feedback]

10:33.110 --> 10:34.372
[ baby coos]

10:38.159 --> 10:40.944
Who's a little carpenter?

10:41.031 --> 10:43.947
Jamie's a little carpenter.

10:49.736 --> 10:51.825
You come with me.

10:51.912 --> 10:54.828
I had it. The gift. Perfect.

10:54.915 --> 10:55.698
Destroyed.

10:55.785 --> 10:57.178
That little one.

10:57.265 --> 10:58.570
Bad diapers!

10:58.658 --> 10:59.484
Come on, now.

10:59.571 --> 11:01.051
What happened happened.

11:01.138 --> 11:03.184
The main thing is
I'm here to help.

11:03.271 --> 11:04.359
Need help. Can't do it alone.

11:04.446 --> 11:05.795
Now, tomorrow you'll be

11:05.882 --> 11:07.754
on your way to work
when you'll realize

11:07.841 --> 11:09.407
that your favorite
son, Reese,

11:09.494 --> 11:11.714
is completely out
of hair-care products.

11:11.801 --> 11:13.107
So you'll put together

11:13.194 --> 11:14.456
a charming gift basket
full of shampoos

11:14.543 --> 11:15.762
and styling gels.

11:15.849 --> 11:16.719
Has to be done.

11:16.806 --> 11:19.156
No question. Get to work.

11:19.243 --> 11:21.898
It's interesting you'd
say that, because, actually,

11:21.985 --> 11:25.380
there are quite a few projects
I have lined up for you.

11:26.424 --> 11:27.730
Oh, but first.

11:28.862 --> 11:31.299
I'd like you to do something
very important for me.

11:31.386 --> 11:32.300
Important. Of course.

11:32.387 --> 11:33.344
It's important.

11:33.431 --> 11:35.085
Yes, it is.

11:35.172 --> 11:37.958
I want you to kiss this.

11:38.915 --> 11:41.439
You know, like you
really mean it.

11:49.273 --> 11:52.320
[ Hal moans softly]

11:52.407 --> 11:54.235
STUFFED CHICKEN
[ mechanical voice]
Let's be friends!

11:54.322 --> 11:57.020
Yes, yes, I'll hold. Thank you.

11:57.107 --> 11:58.674
I hate politics.

11:58.761 --> 12:00.284
The voters don't read.

12:00.371 --> 12:02.069
They don't think for themselves.

12:02.156 --> 12:04.332
They're completely swayed
by the last thing they heard,

12:04.419 --> 12:07.074
whether it's true or not.

12:07.161 --> 12:08.553
Democracy's a failure

12:08.640 --> 12:11.078
because, let's face it:
people are idiots.

12:11.165 --> 12:14.690
I think you'd feel better
about the world, Dewey,

12:14.777 --> 12:16.866
if you had
a programmable zombie robot.

12:16.953 --> 12:17.737
That's right.

12:17.824 --> 12:19.173
I'm looking to replace

12:19.260 --> 12:20.696
the music box
with the ballerina on top.

12:20.783 --> 12:22.872
I wouldn't say broken
so much as vaporized.

12:22.959 --> 12:25.005
My toddler got a hold of it.

12:25.092 --> 12:27.094
Oh, oh. Give me that.

12:27.181 --> 12:28.878
So, anyway, I would really
appreciate it if you could
help me...

12:28.965 --> 12:30.532
[ timer ringing]
[ clucks like chicken]

12:30.619 --> 12:33.056
...a list of local distributors
who might have one.

12:33.143 --> 12:34.928
What are you talking about?
Why on Earth

12:35.015 --> 12:36.364
would I do that?

12:36.451 --> 12:38.366
Listen, the truth is,
I'm pretty desperate here

12:38.453 --> 12:40.455
so if you can just give me...
[ dryer buzzes]

12:40.542 --> 12:42.239
...some information
that can help me track down

12:42.326 --> 12:43.458
another ballerina music box

12:43.545 --> 12:45.242
you can actually

12:45.329 --> 12:47.549
turn this into a very special
anniversary celebration.

12:47.636 --> 12:48.768
LOIS:
Sorry I'm late!

12:49.725 --> 12:52.249
Oh, oh, please, like the orphans

12:52.336 --> 12:54.469
would really see any
of the money I would give you.

12:54.556 --> 12:55.731
Do you have an orphan
there with you?

12:55.818 --> 12:56.906
Could I speak
to one, please?

12:56.993 --> 12:58.125
I didn't think so.

12:58.212 --> 12:59.909
You know what?
You people make me sick.

12:59.996 --> 13:01.781
Damn telemarketers.

13:01.868 --> 13:04.392
Hal, you know what I realized
on the way home?

13:04.479 --> 13:06.481
Our 20th anniversary is
in three days.

13:06.568 --> 13:08.744
Huh. Just three days, huh?

13:08.831 --> 13:10.877
Boy, talk about time flying.
[ laughs]

13:10.964 --> 13:13.314
It'll be here
before you know it.

13:13.401 --> 13:15.185
LOIS:
20 years.

13:15.272 --> 13:18.449
We're really gonna have
to do something special.

13:20.669 --> 13:22.758
[ all chattering excitedly]

13:22.845 --> 13:23.759
She totally did.

13:23.846 --> 13:25.195
I saw her, I swear!

13:25.282 --> 13:26.283
He's a liar!

13:26.370 --> 13:27.763
V-Vote for me!

13:27.850 --> 13:29.112
Stop screaming at me.

13:29.199 --> 13:31.332
You're not
my guidance counselor!

13:31.419 --> 13:34.552
Guys, guys, calm down.
What's going on?

13:34.639 --> 13:36.859
Zoe thinks she'd make
a better President than me,

13:36.946 --> 13:38.295
even though that
it's a known fact

13:38.382 --> 13:39.862
that she eats her own hair lice.

13:39.949 --> 13:41.646
Oh, yeah? Well, I wonder

13:41.733 --> 13:43.866
how the voters would feel
if they knew that Hanson likes

13:43.953 --> 13:45.520
to French kiss

13:45.607 --> 13:48.131
his poodle, and I know
'cause dogs don't lie to me.

13:48.218 --> 13:49.959
What are you doing?

13:50.046 --> 13:51.961
I thought you two were gonna
stay friends, no matter what.

13:52.048 --> 13:53.745
Oh, wake up, Dewey.
There's a little too much

13:53.833 --> 13:55.051
at stake here
to play that game.

13:55.138 --> 13:56.748
Stop it!

13:56.836 --> 13:59.795
The truth is you two
were nominated as a joke,

13:59.882 --> 14:01.928
but you had a chance
to show the rest of the school

14:02.015 --> 14:04.800
that you were better
than Kyle and his friends.

14:04.887 --> 14:06.367
Now you're no different
than they are.

14:07.411 --> 14:08.935
We used to be a team.

14:09.022 --> 14:10.980
You two and the four of me.

14:11.067 --> 14:13.722
We have no idea
who you are anymore.

14:14.766 --> 14:15.855
You guys do what you want.

14:15.942 --> 14:16.986
I'm sick of this.

14:19.293 --> 14:21.469
Hal, you didn't even
touch your pie.

14:21.556 --> 14:23.427
Oh, yeah, I'm saving
that for Reese.

14:27.388 --> 14:29.781
I have something
I want you guys to hear.

14:32.001 --> 14:34.612
I've been practicing,
really practicing, a lot.

14:34.699 --> 14:36.614
And I had an idea for a song.

14:36.701 --> 14:38.616
I don't know
if it's any good or not,

14:38.703 --> 14:40.836
but it really means something
to me.

14:41.924 --> 14:43.273
Do you mind
if I play it for you?

14:43.360 --> 14:44.492
Of course not, Malcolm.

14:44.579 --> 14:47.408
We'd love to hear it.

14:47.495 --> 14:50.367
[ slow, soulful]
♪ No one knows ♪

14:50.454 --> 14:53.849
♪ Just what I've been through ♪

14:53.936 --> 14:58.941
♪ I can't stop the pain
inside me ♪

14:59.028 --> 15:03.119
♪ Now I'm staring
out my window ♪

15:03.206 --> 15:05.252
♪ Children play ♪

15:05.339 --> 15:08.124
♪ They seem so happy ♪

15:08.211 --> 15:14.435
♪ Why are we here,
going nowhere? ♪

15:14.522 --> 15:21.442
♪ Why does my life
feel so empty? ♪

15:21.529 --> 15:23.705
♪ Meow, meow, meow, meow,
meow, meow, meow, meow ♪

15:23.792 --> 15:25.620
♪ Meow, meow, meow, meow
meow, meow, meow, meow. ♪

15:25.707 --> 15:26.664
What are you doing?

15:26.751 --> 15:28.666
That's the Meow Mix song.

15:28.753 --> 15:30.755
♪ No one knows just
what I've been through ♪

15:30.842 --> 15:32.670
♪ Meow, meow, meow, meow,
meow, meow, meow, meow. ♪

15:32.757 --> 15:34.629
♪ Now I'm staring
out the window ♪

15:34.716 --> 15:36.631
♪ Meow, meow, meow, meow,
meow, meow, meow, meow. ♪

15:36.718 --> 15:38.328
♪ I want chicken,
I want liver ♪

15:38.415 --> 15:40.374
♪ Meow Mix, Meow Mix,
please deliver ♪

15:40.461 --> 15:42.289
♪ Now you know the cat's meow ♪

15:42.376 --> 15:43.812
♪ Is Meow Mix,
Meow Mix, Meow Mix... ♪

15:43.899 --> 15:45.466
And then the cat
kind of walk...
[ yowls]

15:45.553 --> 15:47.642
Okay, okay, stop it!

15:47.729 --> 15:50.427
God! I just spent two days
of my life

15:50.514 --> 15:52.647
rewriting the Meow Mix song.

15:52.734 --> 15:54.997
I poured my heart into this.

15:55.084 --> 15:57.347
I actually got tears
in my eyes writing it.

15:57.434 --> 15:59.436
How pathetic is that?

15:59.523 --> 16:02.396
I clearly have even less talent
than you gave me credit for.

16:05.616 --> 16:07.270
Should we tell him
the kid recovered

16:07.357 --> 16:08.489
from the tick bite,

16:08.576 --> 16:09.446
and the trip to
Europe's off?

16:09.533 --> 16:11.709
No.

16:11.796 --> 16:14.277
Let him return
the guitar first.

16:15.452 --> 16:18.020
[ sighs]

16:18.107 --> 16:19.195
Got to get this.

16:19.282 --> 16:20.588
It has to.

16:20.675 --> 16:23.330
Okay, let's see
what you've got here.

16:24.679 --> 16:25.854
These aren't even letters.

16:25.941 --> 16:27.551
Why did I think

16:27.638 --> 16:29.205
a zombie could write an essay
on Johnny Tremain?

16:29.292 --> 16:30.511
Come on. We might
as well go to bed.

16:30.598 --> 16:31.599
No, don't. Wait.

16:31.686 --> 16:32.817
Have to get the answer.

16:32.904 --> 16:34.167
Dad, I'm not gonna be able

16:34.254 --> 16:35.081
to help you
with an idea for Mom.

16:35.168 --> 16:36.473
And the other ideas I have

16:36.560 --> 16:37.518
for you are just gonna land us
in jail.

16:37.605 --> 16:38.693
You can help.

16:38.780 --> 16:39.868
You're the one
I can talk to.

16:39.955 --> 16:41.130
You're my guy.

16:41.217 --> 16:44.090
Really?

16:44.177 --> 16:47.267
I thought
Malcolm was your favorite.

16:47.354 --> 16:48.790
No. The smart
one scares me.

16:48.877 --> 16:49.965
You're normal.

16:50.052 --> 16:51.271
Like me.

16:51.358 --> 16:53.360
Is that why you grabbed me?

16:54.448 --> 16:56.493
You're my guy.

16:58.582 --> 16:59.801
I don't care
if everyone thinks

16:59.888 --> 17:01.411
this election is a joke.

17:01.498 --> 17:03.631
I'm not screwing around anymore.
You got to vote

17:03.718 --> 17:05.111
for me, please.

17:05.198 --> 17:07.896
Whatever you heard
about me is all lies...

17:07.983 --> 17:09.157
Hey, Dewey.

17:09.244 --> 17:10.898
Hi.

17:10.986 --> 17:12.857
I've never dressed up as
that Girl Scout for Halloween.

17:12.944 --> 17:14.598
I've been thinking
about what you said.

17:14.685 --> 17:16.731
You're right: we are better
than these jerks.

17:16.818 --> 17:19.342
I'm gonna throw the election
so Zoe will win.

17:19.429 --> 17:21.300
She'll become popular.

17:21.387 --> 17:23.215
Than she can tell us
what we're missing

17:23.303 --> 17:25.000
instead of us having
to imagine it.

17:25.087 --> 17:26.219
How are you gonna do that?

17:26.306 --> 17:28.221
I haven't slept in two days,

17:28.308 --> 17:30.266
and I've been staring
into a strobe light

17:30.353 --> 17:31.876
for the last 20 minutes.

17:31.963 --> 17:34.531
It's time for everyone else
to meet the Hanson

17:34.618 --> 17:38.361
that until now,
only paramedics have seen.

17:38.448 --> 17:40.798
What are you smiling at, Hooper?

17:40.885 --> 17:43.410
I'm not kidding. Vote for me.
Damn it. Just do it!

17:43.497 --> 17:44.976
Thank you, Kyle.

17:45.064 --> 17:47.675
And now for our next candidate,
David Hanson.

